COTS (also C.O.T.S.) is an acronym for Commercial Off The Shelf.
Produts readily available for sale through commercial channels and or from commercial partners.
The product is developed based on a generic idea or brief or requirements list, and targeted to meet the requirements of a defined group of customers (these could be anything from children, through music lovers to specialist service providers in any industry).
Production is set up such that repetitive manufacturing facilitates lower cost than what would be possible for one off items or limited series.
Marketing and sales of the product is conducted accross the assumed customer base, e.g. one or more consumer groups or one or more industry segments